  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1635",
  "title": "ScrollTo+Pagination: Introduce a small delay before scrolling top",
  "body": "**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\n\r\nFeature.\r\n\r\n**What is the current behavior?**\r\n\r\nWhen using both the `ScrollTo` and `Pagination` widgets, it scrolls so fast to the top that it's actually pretty confusing to understand that your click worked. I would expect a visual feedback explaining my page 2 will load (by selecting it for instance) before it actually scrolls.\r\n\r\nOf course, it's more complex that just adding a `setTimeout` in the `ScrollTo` component because we would like to select the next page before the API actually answers. Something like:\r\n - click on the next page\r\n - change the selected/highlighted page number (before the API comes back with the new page)\r\n - query the API\r\n - scroll top\r\n\r\nWould love to hear what you guys think. cc @Shipow @LucasC ",
